<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FC81FE07FA940994" blockId="11.[828,1457,454,1277]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FC81FE07FC3D0AF4" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Myxococcus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="llanfairpwllgwyngyllgogerychwyrndrobwllllantysiliogogogochensis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC81FE07FC3D0AF4" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Myxococcus llanfairpwllgwyngyllgogerychwyrndrobwllllantysiliogogogochensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (llan.fair.pwll.gwyn.gyll.gog.er.ych.wyrn.dro.bwllll.ant.ysil.iog.ogogoch.en’sis. N.L. masc. adj. llanfairpwllgwyngyllgogerychwyrndrobwllllantysiliogogogo chensis, pertaining to llanfairpwllgwyngyllgogerychwyrndrobwllllantysiliogogogoch, reflecting its isolation from soil collected in that parish [gridref 
<geoCoordinate id="EE3AFED26475D730FB31FD47FB270994" box="[1164,1254,646,669]" degrees="53.22" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" precision="555" value="53.22">53.22 N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE3AFED26475D730FB50FD47FA840994" box="[1261,1349,646,669]" degrees="4.19" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" precision="555" value="-4.19">4.19 W</geoCoordinate>
]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FCE4FD67FC5A0FF4" blockId="11.[828,1457,454,1277]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
<subSubSection id="C314CB9E6475D730FCE4FD67FACC0F74" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" type="description">
Vegetative cells are Gram-negative bacilli tapering slightly at the ends, measuring 
<quantity id="4CF635F06475D730FB8DFD07FB5109D4" box="[1072,1168,709,733]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" unit="m" value="0.5" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.4">
0.4–0.6 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FB3EFD04FB5109D4" bold="true" box="[1155,1168,709,733]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m 4.0–7.0 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FAA7FD04FAE609D4" bold="true" box="[1306,1319,709,733]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">m</emphasis>
m in electron micrographs. Colonies exhibit swarming motility and appear pale brown on VY-2 agar (w/v 0.5% dried baker’s yeast, 0.1% CaCl 
<subScript id="178A9A506475D730FC0EFCF1FC7C0836" attach="left" box="[947,957,816,831]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">2</subScript>
2H 
<subScript id="178A9A506475D730FC5CFCF1FC2A0836" attach="both" box="[993,1003,816,831]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">2</subScript>
O, and 1.5% agar). Fruiting bodies are irregular spheroids, orange in color. Aerobic growth was observed at 30 and 35 C and at pH 5.0–9.0. Growth was unaffected by the addition of 1–4% NaCl. Hydrolyzes esculin, gelatin, 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC02FC67FC0D08B4" box="[959,972,934,957]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">p</emphasis>
-nitrophenyl- 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FBECFC67FB9E08B4" box="[1105,1119,934,957]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">B</emphasis>
-D- galactopyranoside, and urea. Assimilates 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC06FC07FC0A08D4" box="[955,971,966,989]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">N</emphasis>
-acetyl-glucosamine, adipate, arabinose, glucose, malate, maltose, mannitol, mannose, and phenyl acetate. Cells prey with low efficiency upon 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FAAEFBC7FA570F14" authority="TOP" authorityName="TOP" box="[1299,1430,1030,1053]" class="Gammaproteobacteria" family="Enterobacteriaceae" genus="Escherichia" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Enterobacteriales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="coli">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FAAEFBC7FA960F14" box="[1299,1367,1030,1053]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">E. coli</emphasis>
TOP
</taxonomicName>
10, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FC81FBE7FBD60F34" authority="DSM" authorityName="DSM" box="[828,1047,1062,1085]" class="Actinobacteria" family="Microbacteriaceae" genus="Clavibacter" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Actinomycetales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Actinobacteria" rank="species" species="nebraskensis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FC81FBE7FC1F0F34" box="[828,990,1062,1085]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Cl. nebraskensis</emphasis>
DSM
</taxonomicName>
7483, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FB33FBE7FB320F34" box="[1166,1267,1062,1085]" class="Ustilaginomycetes" family="Ustilaginaceae" genus="Ustilago" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ustilaginales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="maydis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FB33FBE7FB320F34" box="[1166,1267,1062,1085]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">U. maydis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. DNA 
<collectionCode id="ED1F00D06475D730FA8AFBE7FA9B0F34" box="[1335,1370,1062,1085]" country="0" name="Goucher College" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">GC</collectionCode>
content is 68.7 mol%. The draft genome sequence of 
<collectionCode id="ED1F00D06475D730FA80FB87FAA50F54" box="[1341,1380,1094,1117]" country="Australia" name="Australian Museum" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" type="Museum">AM</collectionCode>
401 
<superScript id="7C7B355D6475D730FA31FB81FA540F46" attach="left" box="[1420,1429,1088,1103]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
<collectionCode id="ED1F00D06475D730FA31FB81FA540F46" box="[1420,1429,1088,1103]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">T</collectionCode>
</superScript>
is available from GenBank (accession 
<collectionCode id="ED1F00D06475D730FB13FBA7FB2D0F74" box="[1198,1260,1126,1149]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">VIFM</collectionCode>
01).
</subSubSection>
